= Installing Git =
Git is a distributed control management software where all the [http://www.freedesktop.org freedesktop.org] projects are hosted. In order to get the latest code available for the unstable version of apoc you need to grab it using git. You can see more instructions on how to get the latest source on the [:Apoc/Downloads download section].

[[TableOfContents()]]
== Git on Ubuntu/Debian ==
Look for the package git-core on the Synaptic package management tool, or type this as root:
{{{
# apt-get install git-core
}}}

== Git on Fedora ==
Type this as root:
{{{
# yum install git-core
}}}

== Git on Solaris ==
To install Git on Solaris we provide a set of stream packages built from the [http://pkgbuild.sourceforge.net Spec Files Extra] repository. (Thanks to Laszlo Peters for the SFE project and the help on building the binary packages). Git depends on [http://curl.haxx.se/ curl], so you need to install the curl binary too.
